import Mathlib

/--
Let U ‚äÜ ‚ÑÇ be a domain and f : U ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ be holomorphic. In Lean/Mathlib we express
"holomorphic on U" by `DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U` (complex differentiable on the open set U),
and "analytic on U" by `AnalyticOn ‚ÑÇ f U`.

This file states the standard fact that a complex-differentiable function on an open
set is analytic on that set.
-/

variable {U : Set ‚ÑÇ} {f : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ}

theorem holomorphic_on_implies_analytic_on (hU : IsOpen U) (h : DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U) :
  AnalyticOn ‚ÑÇ f U := by sorry

import Mathlib

/--
Let U ‚äÜ ‚ÑÇ be a domain and f : U ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ be holomorphic. In Lean/Mathlib we express
"holomorphic on U" by `DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U` (complex differentiable on the open set U),
and "analytic on U" by `AnalyticOn ‚ÑÇ f U`.

This file states the standard fact that a complex-differentiable function on an open
set is analytic on that set.
-/

theorem holomorphic_on_implies_analytic_on {U : Set ‚ÑÇ} {f : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ} (hU : IsOpen U)
  (h : DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U) : AnalyticOn ‚ÑÇ f U := by sorry
